Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.00,0:01:18.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,[历史频道] 第二季 第七集 天体生物学\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}[History Channel] The UniverseⅡ 07of19 Astrobiology
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.16,0:01:23.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,生命 在宇宙中是否是十分罕见的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Life, is it rare in our universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.12,0:01:28.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还是就在银河动物园里挤满了各种生物呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or is space a galactic zoo, teeming with all sorts of creatures?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.42,0:01:33.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,大家都对外星生命有着这种图像化的概念\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everybody has this sort of iconic view of the aliens.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.63,0:01:37.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们都是些阴沉的小家伙 大大的眼睛 小小的鼻子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're going to be little gray guys with big eyeballs and small noses.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.22,0:01:39.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是这样 但是 我不这么认为\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, maybe, but l don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.18,0:01:46.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在遥远的行星上 生命没准就是贼眼大大的微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On far-off planets, life may be as far out as buggy-eyed microbes...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.81,0:01:50.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或者就是银河蝠鲼之类的科幻海怪\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or sci-fi sea monsters like galactic manta rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.44,0:01:56.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其它则可归类为神经机械有机体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Others may be home to cybernetic organisms...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.44,0:01:59.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,生物和机械的混血儿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hybrids of biology and machines.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.78,0:02:05.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,理清超级高等外星生命思路的一个方法\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One way to get a handle on thinking about super advanced aliens...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.45,0:02:08.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是尝试想象一下我们自己未来的情景\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is to try to imagine the possibilities of our own future.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.33,0:02:10.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也许会是机器复合人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it'll be machine-enabled humans.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.38,0:02:15.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我感觉自己已经成了机器复合人了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l feel like l've already become a machine-human hybrid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.46,0:02:18.51,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我的意思是 我这台随身携带的手提电脑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l mean, l have this laptop computer that l take with me everywhere...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.55,0:02:21.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它俨然成了我大脑的第三半区了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is really kind of the third hemisphere of my brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.47,0:02:22.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我身体甚至都在逐步变成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}My body is even changing...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.68,0:02:26.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,用手提电脑那种人的外形了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and becoming sort of shaped like a person using a laptop computer...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.43,0:02:28.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 我正在变成人机复合体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and so l'm becoming a Homo laptopicus.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.85,0:02:32.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能宇宙到处都存在着生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's likely that the universe is full of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.81,0:02:35.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们尚无法证明我们不是孤独的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We don't have evidence yet that we're not alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.69,0:02:37.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们来到那里 来看看\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we're out there, and we're looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.15,0:02:42.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,提起搜寻外星生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it comes to hunting for alien life...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.49,0:02:45.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星科学家 音乐家戴维·格林斯彭\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}planetary scientist and musician David Grinspoon...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.04,0:02:48.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,弹奏出不同的节奏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}walks to a different beat.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.13,0:02:57.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我就想知道关于外星生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l do wonder, in terms of extraterrestrial life...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.09,0:02:59.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是否有音乐或音乐之类的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whether they'll have music or something like music.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.55,0:03:04.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,音乐本质上是声波和韵律\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Music is fundamentally waves and rhythms...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.93,0:03:08.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,属于我们宇宙的本性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's sort of the nature of our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.18,0:03:11.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,事实上是某种乐感\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is a certain musicality ofjust the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.52,0:03:17.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是所有的颤动 声波 韵律 音调\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it's all vibrations and waves and rhythms and modulated tones.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.65,0:03:23.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 我可以想象出 当然这只是我的异想天开\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So l can imagine, and this is just my wild fantasy...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.16,0:03:26.12,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比方说遥远未来的世界音乐\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}some analogy to world music far in the future...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.16,0:03:30.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是我们的音乐文化和外星音乐文化交织在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where we're mixing our musical cultures with alien musical cultures.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.12,0:03:35.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我想你要是与不同的科学家交流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l think you'll get many different shades of astrobiology...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.54,0:03:37.50,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就会看到天体生物学的各种差异\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you talk to different scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.55,0:03:40.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 在大致的目标上我认为你我会有很多共识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but l think you'll get a lot of agreement on the broad goals.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.72,0:03:44.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们希望发现外星生命 但是同时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We want to find life else where, but in the meantime...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.22,0:03:47.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们对地球的生命史 还仍有待进一步认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we're learning a lot about the history of life on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.64,0:03:52.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在天体生物学领域里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the field of astrobiology...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.06,0:03:56.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻外星生命的重要目标之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the fundamental goals in searching for life else where...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.48,0:04:00.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就是首先要搞明白地球生命是如何演化的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is first figuring out how life evolved here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.82,0:04:05.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天体生物学一个重大的未解之谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One of the big unsolved mysteries in astrobiology, of course...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.70,0:04:08.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,当然就是生命何以在地球上诞生\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is how life got started on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.28,0:04:11.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 我们一旦搞明白了我们就能够洞察\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because if we can understand that, then we would have some insight...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.75,0:04:13.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,生命是否已经能够诞生于别的地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into whether it could have gotten started else where.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.71,0:04:22.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球运行于所谓的适居带"habitable zone"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth orbits in what's called the "habitable zone."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.42,0:04:26.47,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个太空区域的环境有利于生命的形成\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's a region of space where conditions are favorable for life forms...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.51,0:04:28.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些我们知道都能在地球上看到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we know can be found on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.14,0:04:34.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们刚好处于与太阳适当的距离\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are at just the right distance from the Sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.23,0:04:36.77,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以我们的海洋不会蒸发掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so our oceans don't evaporate...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.81,0:04:40.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的温度不太冷也不太热\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our temperatures are not too hot or too cold...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.44,0:04:45.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们在大气层里有氧气所以我们能够呼吸\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we have oxygen in our atmosphere so we can breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.74,0:04:52.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球一直是各种生命的宇宙天堂\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Earth's been a cosmic paradise for all types of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.25,0:04:55.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,从小的单细胞生物如细菌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from small single-celled organisms, such as bacteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.96,0:05:01.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到大的多细胞哺乳动物 包括人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to large multicellular mammals, including man.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.80,0:05:07.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,据认为我们地球的所有生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's believed that all life on our planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.22,0:05:10.89,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,都是传承于约34到38亿年前的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}descended from a single common microbial ancestry...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.97,0:05:16.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一个共同的微生物老祖宗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}approximately 3.4 to 3.8 billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.27,0:05:21.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是那个微生物是如何开始的始终是个谜\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how that microbe came into being remains puzzling.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.82,0:05:29.45,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,寻求答案的一个方法就是寻找古代岩石\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One way to search for answers is to look for ancient rocks...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.49,0:05:33.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那里微生物会留下它们生存的蛛丝马迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where microbes leave trace evidence of their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.71,0:05:40.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地质学是了解地球生命起源和进化的关键手段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geology is a crucial tool...for understanding the origins and evolution of life on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.25,0:05:42.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为地球生命的历史记载\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because the historical record of life on Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.00,0:05:46.72,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几乎完整地记录在我们脚下的岩石里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is almost entirely recorded in the rocks that we walk on.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.10,0:05:56.18,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地质学家阿比盖尔·奥尔伍德的生命起源发现之旅\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}GeologistAbigail Allwood'sjourney to discover the origins of life...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.23,0:05:59.60,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,走出并没有超出她自己后院有多远\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}took her no farther than her own backyard.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.52,0:06:04.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,西澳大利亚的皮尔巴拉地区\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Pilbara region ofWestAustralia...
