Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.17,0:30:47.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为 我们真的不知道我们在找的是什么\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}'cause we don't really know what we're looking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.97,0:30:50.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,依靠新的科技\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Armed with new technologies...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.01,0:30:55.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天体生物学家已经拓展了对外星生命的搜寻\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astrobiologists have widened their search for extraterrestrial life.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:56.22,0:31:02.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,下一个前沿包括我们整个银河系及其以外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The next frontier includes our entire Milky Way galaxy and beyond.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.03,0:31:13.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天体生物学正撤回到现代科学的范围\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Astrobiology is pushing back the boundaries of modern science.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.74,0:31:20.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,研究人员现在有了定位日外行星的技术手段\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Researchers now have the technological instruments...to locate exoplanets.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.62,0:31:25.75,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些都是存在于太阳系外的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These are planets that exist outside our solar system.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.21,0:31:31.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,日外行星需要经过若干次测试\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Exoplanets need to pass several tests...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.68,0:31:35.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,目的是为了审视是否适合类地生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in order to be considered suitable for Earthlike life.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.31,0:31:41.10,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,最重要的是它们需要在一个适宜居住的地带\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most importantly, they need to be within a habitable zone...
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.14,0:31:46.57,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,中央有一颗恒星 就像我们有太阳能以保持有液态水\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a central star, like our Sun, in order to support liquid water.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.19,0:31:49.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的恒星恰到好处\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our star is just right.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:49.36,0:31:51.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不是太热也不是太冷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's not too hot, and it's not too cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.32,0:31:56.28,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 我们就恰好处在这个生命得以进化的理想之地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so we're just right in this perfect area where life was able to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:59.33,0:32:05.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,2008年航天局发射了一个太空望远镜叫做开普勒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln 2008, NASA plans to launch a space telescope called Kepler...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.29,0:32:08.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,来搜索地球般大小的类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to search for terrestrial Earth-sized planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.42,0:32:14.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,航天器上的仪器能够侦测到日外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The spacecraft's instruments will be able to detect exoplanets...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.80,0:32:18.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过测量恒星的光变曲线的变化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by measuring changes in a star"s light curve...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.81,0:32:23.02,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦行星在恒星与航天器之间经过\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a planet passes between the star and the spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.94,0:32:28.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,杰夫·马西是世界上主要的行星猎手之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Geoff Marcy is one of the world's leading planet hunters.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.11,0:32:33.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们估计光我们的银河系就有约500亿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We would estimate that there are some fif ty billion...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.86,0:32:40.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或者600亿颗类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe sixty billion Earthlike planets...within just our Milky Way galaxy alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.41,0:32:42.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,别忘了我们的银河系\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and remember, our Milky Way galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.71,0:32:47.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只是数百上千亿个星系中的一个\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is just one of hundreds of billions of galaxies out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.04,0:32:48.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它们都差不多与银河系相仿\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}more or less like our Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.00,0:32:51.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此我们宇宙中的类地行星的数量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So the number of Earthlike planets in our universe...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:51.71,0:32:54.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,几乎是不计其数的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a nearly uncountable number.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.51,0:33:01.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而找到日外行星对于天体生物学来说只成功了一半\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But locating exoplanets is only half the battle for an astrobiologist.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.43,0:33:03.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在未来的20年里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln the next twenty years...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.39,0:33:06.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,航天局将会发射类地行星探测器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASAwill launch the Terrestrial Planet Finder.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.11,0:33:13.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这个高灵敏太空望远镜的集合体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This collection of highly sensitive space telescopes...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.36,0:33:17.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将会确认行星是否具有合适的大气层气体\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will actually recognize if a planet has the right atmospheric gases...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.83,0:33:23.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如水蒸汽 二氧化碳 甲烷 臭氧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}such as water vapor, carbon dioxide, methane, and ozone...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.00,0:33:27.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有维持类地生命所必需的物质\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all necessary to sustain Earthlike life.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.59,0:33:32.88,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有了图像我们就能拿着那颗行星所发出的光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With that picture, we can then take the light from that planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.92,0:33:35.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,将其延展成各种颜色或波长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spread it out into all of its colors or wavelengths:
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.80,0:33:38.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蓝 绿 黄 红甚至到红外线\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}blue, green, yellow, red, even to the infrared...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.43,0:33:41.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,分析那光的化学成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and analyze that light for the chemical composition...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.72,0:33:45.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至还有可能那颗行星的生物成分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe even the biological composition of that planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:45.31,0:33:50.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们就有可能发现各种生命的痕迹\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we might find are signs of life in a variety offorms.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.52,0:33:52.23,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,比如氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For example, oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.53,0:33:59.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,要产生大型类地生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When it comes to producing larger Earthlike life...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.82,0:34:02.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星或卫星就离不开氧气了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a planet or moon needs oxygen.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.45,0:34:09.42,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,34亿年前我们地球唯一的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}3.4 billion years ago, the only life on our planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.46,0:34:12.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是单细胞微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}were single-celled microbial organisms.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.88,0:34:17.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是随着这个原始生命吸收太阳能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But as this primitive life absorbed energy from the sun...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.05,0:34:22.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它形成了一种绿色色素叫做叶绿素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it formed a green pigment called chlorophyll.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.14,0:34:28.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这就产生了光合作用 一种化学过程\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This produced photosynthesis, a chemical process...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.98,0:34:32.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,能将二氧化碳和水转化成能量\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which converts carbon dioxide and water into energy...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.40,0:34:35.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,同时氧气作为其废产物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with oxygen as a waste product.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.57,0:34:39.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,单细胞生物进化成蓝细菌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Single-celled organisms evolved into cyanobacteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.28,0:34:41.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,地球上最早的生物结构\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one of the Earth's earliest structures.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:43.83,0:34:48.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,蓝细菌将大量的氧注入到海洋和大气中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cyanobacteria injected vast amounts of oxygen into the oceans and air.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.17,0:34:55.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,新生命出现了 经过多样化和进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}New life emerged, which diversified and developed...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.76,0:35:00.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,变成了众多的多细胞物种 最终变成了人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into large, multicellular species and, eventually, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.30,0:35:05.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的地球大气层中就会没有氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our Earth would not have oxygen in the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.26,0:35:09.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,只要没有植物的生长\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if it were not for plant life, by photosynthesis...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.60,0:35:14.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,光合作用所产生的氧气就会氧化岩石而消失殆尽\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}generating the oxygen that other wise would oxidize rocks and vanish.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.86,0:35:20.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以氧是地球的生物标志\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So oxygen is a biomarker for the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.24,0:35:22.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们能够审视另一颗类地行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lfwe could examine another Earthlike planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.87,0:35:25.58,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,并在其大气层里发现氧气\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and detect oxygen in its atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.62,0:35:29.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就成了一个关键的标记 但还不是决定性的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it would be one key sign... not yet definitive...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.37,0:35:31.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而是争论的一个要素\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but one element of the argument...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.37,0:35:35.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就是 行星也还要有光合作用的生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that that planet, too, has photosynthetic life.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.84,0:35:41.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在航天局的阿姆斯研究中心\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At NASA's Ames Research Center...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.59,0:35:45.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,天体化学家李·倍布特及其同事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}astrochemist Lee Bebout and her colleagues...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.47,0:35:49.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,正在一个温室里培养含氧生态系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are cultivating oxygen-bearing ecosystems in a greenhouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.64,0:35:54.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些是微生物垫 复杂的微生物群落\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're microbial mats, complex microbe communities...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:54.52,0:35:58.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,常见于高盐度水体和碳酸盐海滩的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}often found on muddy and sandy sediment surfaces...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.11,0:36:01.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,淤泥和沙质的沉积物表面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in hyper-salty waters and carbonate beaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.70,0:36:08.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这些微生物垫是地球上已知最古老的生态系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These microbial mats are the oldest known living ecosystems on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.04,0:36:15.29,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,倍布特想知道 这些有可能存在于其他行星的微生物是否\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Bebout wants to know if these microbes could exist on other planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.33,0:36:20.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,会产生氧气 从而让生命得以进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}producing oxygen, thereby enabling life to evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.30,0:36:26.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们知道随着氧气生产的出现\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We know that, with the advent of oxygen production...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.26,0:36:29.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,通过光合作用这些微生物生态系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}through photosynthesis, these microbial ecosystems...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.81,0:36:33.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,尤其是蓝细菌开始改变我们的大气层\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in particular the cyanobacteria, began to change our atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.52,0:36:36.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们非常好奇那是如何发生的？是如何变迁的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're very curious how that happened, how that transitioned...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.02,0:36:39.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,是如何改造和传播的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how these microbes adapted and spread...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.36,0:36:42.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,到种类繁多充斥了我们地球的各个地方\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to diversif y and fill so many niches on our planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.20,0:36:46.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这很重要 有助于我们判定要找的那些行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is important in helping us decide what to look for on other places...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.03,0:36:49.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,也就是火星或其它日外行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}say, Mars or other extraterrestrial places.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.71,0:36:59.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果生命存在于我们银河系或遥远的星系里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf life exists far off in our galaxy or in distant galaxies...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.88,0:37:02.63,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么它真的会是地球这样的呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will it truly be Earthlike?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.88,0:37:07.76,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在我们地球上所有的生命都具有DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On our planet, all life contains DNA...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.10,0:37:14.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,掌握每一个生命蓝本的一长串分子\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a long chain of molecules that holds the blueprint for every living thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.10,0:37:19.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,它使得生命复制和分枝\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt allows life to duplicate and branch out...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:19.32,0:37:22.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,实质上是在创造生命之树\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}essentially creating the tree of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.03,0:37:24.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而存不存在选择呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But are there alternatives?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:27.32,0:37:30.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许另外的世界里的生命 还是碳水为基的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe life on another world is still carbon and water-based...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.58,0:37:32.83,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是根本就不适用DNA\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but doesn't use DNA at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.87,0:37:36.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许它使用完全不同的分子类型来存储信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Maybe it uses a completely different type of molecule to store information.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.00,0:37:38.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将是非常让人兴奋的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That would be very exciting.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.38,0:37:44.59,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那有无可能存在无需DNA 碳 水的生命呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And could there be life that doesn't require DNA, carbon, or water?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.84,0:37:49.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能我们地球是那种蹩脚的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt may be that ours is kind of a crappy planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.18,0:37:50.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,相反外面的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared to what's out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.43,0:37:51.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有可能存在着其他行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that there may be other planets...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.47,0:37:54.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对于高等生命要更加适宜得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that are much more optimized for advanced life.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.44,0:37:59.48,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我好多做天体生物学研究的同事\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Many of my colleagues, which are doing astrobiological research...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.52,0:38:04.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们在寻找的生命 说的刻薄点 我要说可能是傻瓜生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they're looking for life that, unkindly, l might typif y as stupid life.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.15,0:38:05.74,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们多半是在寻找微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're looking for microbes mostly.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.78,0:38:07.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,或许是稍微大一点的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There may be something a little bit bigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.41,0:38:12.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有些天体生物学家希望不期碰上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some astrobiologists want a close encounter...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.12,0:38:14.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,的东西不只是微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with something more than just a microbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.12,0:38:24.05,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们寻找的智能生命或许甚至比我们还要聪明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They're looking for intelligent life that's perhaps even smarter than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.22,0:38:35.68,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,生命的探寻已不止寻找粘糊糊的细菌\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The search for life extends beyond looking for slimy bacteria.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.19,0:38:41.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在天体生物学中 一队技艺高超的科学家\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ln astrobiology, a crack team of scientists...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:41.98,0:38:45.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,希望接触到更加显赫的东西\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wants to make contact with something much grander.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.82,0:38:50.16,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻地外文明 [SETI] 顾名思义 就是搜寻太空智能生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SETl, of course, is looking for intelligent life in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.20,0:38:51.61,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是并不止于此\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but it doesn't just stop there.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.66,0:38:53.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们必须不光是有智慧\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They have to be not only intelligent...
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.70,0:38:55.66,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而且他们还必须具有科技能力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they have to be technologically competent.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.00,0:39:03.54,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻地外文明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Search for Extraterrestrial lntelligence lnstitute...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.59,0:39:07.71,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,简称SETI 利用无线电技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}better known as SETl, uses radio technology...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:07.76,0:39:11.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,监听外星文明的无线电泄漏\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to listen for radio leaks from alien civilizations.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.01,0:39:16.31,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其基于的假设是人类需要沟通\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lt's based on the premise that humans need to communicate.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.35,0:39:20.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 或许外星人种也希望传送他们的信息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So perhaps alien nations also want to get their message out.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.69,0:39:25.90,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们争取做的只是尽力监听信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What we try and do is simply try and eavesdrop on signals...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.94,0:39:29.32,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们用天线截获的无线电波\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}either radio waves that we could pick up with our antennas...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.36,0:39:31.36,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,还有闪烁的激光\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}orflashing laser lights.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:31.41,0:39:35.24,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们可能会利用强大的激光器对准我们的方向发射光束\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They might be using big lasers to aim pulses of light in our direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.04,0:39:39.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我不是人类\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l am not man.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.46,0:39:40.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我是微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l am microbe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.96,0:39:43.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我还是来自搜寻地外文明研究所的塞思·肖斯塔克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l'm also Seth Shostak for the SETl lnstitute...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.71,0:39:45.38,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的任务是了解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}whose mission is to understand...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:45.42,0:39:47.17,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,宇宙生命的属性和起源\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the nature and origin of life in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.21,0:39:49.67,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我是莫莉·本特利 欢迎收听"我们孤独吗？"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And l'm Molly Bentley. Welcome to "Are We Alone?"
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.72,0:39:54.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们要提醒你 生命要多于你在当地动物园所看到的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We'll remind you that there's more to life...than just what you find at your local zoo.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:57.18,0:40:00.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在搜寻地外文明研究所资深天文学家塞思·肖斯塔克\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}At SETl, senior astronomer Seth Shostak...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.98,0:40:04.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,主持一档定期的播客广播节目\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}hosts a regular radio show that's podcasted.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:04.90,0:40:06.82,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们正在监听微生物\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're buggin' out with microbes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.86,0:40:08.98,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,全都与你相伴在一起\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are so many cohabitating with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.03,0:40:11.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你在收听的是"给我一个细菌"\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You're listening to "Hand Me A Microbe."
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.70,0:40:13.53,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,肖斯塔克主持节目生动活泼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Shostak broadcasts lively...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.57,0:40:17.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 在将科学有关的消息提供给地球人的同时\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}yet informative science-related news to Earthlings...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.24,0:40:22.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其他高等文明也有能力收听到\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as well as other advanced civilizations that have the means to listen in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.92,0:40:25.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,辛西娅·菲利普斯 感谢你的加入\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Cynthia Phillips, thanks forjoining me today.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.25,0:40:28.00,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们非常喜欢电台的收听\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We are so fond of radio for listening...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.05,0:40:32.34,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们创办每周一次的广播节目 某种意义上是在播送\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we started a weekly radio show in which we, in a sense, broadcast.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.38,0:40:34.97,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,很多人对搜寻地外文明感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are a lot of people who are interested in SETl...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:35.01,0:40:37.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因为大家对外星人的兴趣不亚于\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because everybody's interested in aliens in the same way...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.60,0:40:39.85,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对恐龙的兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that just about everybody's interested in dinosaurs.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.89,0:40:41.52,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,人们就是对此感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}People are just interested in that.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:41.56,0:40:43.56,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此我们努力利用这样一个事实\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So we're trying to take advantage of the fact...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.60,0:40:45.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们对我们做的感兴趣\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they're interested in what we do...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.40,0:40:48.06,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,让他们感兴趣于某些更广泛的主题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to get them interested in some broader subjects...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.11,0:40:50.15,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,对科学和技术\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in science and also technology.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:53.65,0:40:57.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,搜寻地外文明 自1960年代以来就一直在监听信号\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}SETl has been listening for signals since the 1960s...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.45,0:41:00.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,然而 从未收到过外星人来的讯息\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but E.T. hasn't phoned in.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.12,0:41:06.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,这种沉默已经激起了怀疑\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This silence has fueled skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.09,0:41:10.96,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会发现很多具有生命的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're going to find lots of planets with life.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:11.01,0:41:14.13,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我猜测智慧相当罕见\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l'm guessing that intelligence will be rare...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.18,0:41:17.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是他们将和人类一样聪明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but they won't be smart in the way that humans are smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:17.05,0:41:18.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那将是罕见的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's going to be rare.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.05,0:41:21.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是另一方面那只是我的直觉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But, again, that's just my intuition.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.39,0:41:24.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,外星人不可能快于光速到达这里\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Aliens can't get here faster than the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:24.31,0:41:26.14,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,物理学不允许那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Physics doesn't allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.19,0:41:29.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那就意味着由于我们的广播仅仅只有60年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that means, since we've only been broadcasting...for, say, sixty years...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:29.48,0:41:34.07,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,他们是不可能来自30光年以外的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they can't be coming from a planet more than thirty light-years away.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.11,0:41:37.70,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,30光年以内的恒星数量是相当少的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the number of stars within thirty light-years is pretty small.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.16,0:41:47.08,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们的宇宙已经超过120亿年了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our universe is over twelve billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.12,0:41:51.84,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,行星地球只有约46亿多年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Planet Earth has only been around for over 4.6 billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.55,0:41:59.39,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,因此 存在着比我们年长数百万甚至数十亿年的行星\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Therefore, there are planets millions and billions of years older than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.68,0:42:03.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果银河系外存在着生命的话\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, if there's life beyond the Milky Way galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.60,0:42:09.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,就极有可能比我们先进数百万甚至数十亿年\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it potentially could be millions...to billions of years more advanced than us.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.27,0:42:14.86,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我认为外面确实存在着智能物种\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l think that the truly intelligent species out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.90,0:42:17.20,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果他们曾经和我们不期相遇\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if they ever happened upon us...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.24,0:42:21.49,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么 看待我们可能就像我们看待蚂蚁和细菌那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would maybe regard us as we regard ants or bacteria...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.53,0:42:23.79,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,作为生命的某种原始样本\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as some primitive example of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.54,0:42:29.33,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们遇到的东西会比我们先进得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Anybody we meet is going to be much more advanced than us...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.38,0:42:34.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,至少肯定在文明的历史方面比我们历史悠久得多\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at least certainly much more aged than us...in terms of how long they have been a civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.59,0:42:41.30,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果智慧文明确实存在于地球之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf intelligent civilizations do exist beyond Earth...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.35,0:42:43.01,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,那么他们的模样会怎样呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what would they look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.68,0:42:46.93,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,如果我们在太空中找到智能生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lf we find intelligence in space...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:46.98,0:42:49.73,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,其表现会超出生物智能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's moved on beyond biological intelligence...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:49.77,0:42:52.11,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,而倾向机器智能\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and moved on to machine intelligence.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:53.23,0:42:58.40,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,有思想的机器代表了超越我们百万年的进化\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A thinking machine that represents a million years' evolution...beyond where we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:58.45,0:42:59.78,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,谁知道它是如何打造的？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Who knows how it's built?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.82,0:43:02.91,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,你所知道的一切 就是它有可能非常非常的聪明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All you know is that it might be really, really smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.74,0:43:07.87,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不存在合乎逻辑的理由 认为来自其他世界的机器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's no logical reason why there shouldn't be machines...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:07.91,0:43:10.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,不应该来探索我们的星球\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from other worlds exploring our planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.42,0:43:13.21,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,进入我们的领空\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}coming into our airspace...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:13.25,0:43:16.25,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,甚至可能会以某种方式与我们互动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maybe even attempting to interact with us in some way.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.84,0:43:25.35,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,无论我们发现了细菌的踪迹还是高科技文明\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Whether we find a trace of bacteria or a high-tech civilization...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.39,0:43:28.64,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所有生命的发现都将彻底变革\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any discovery of life will revolutionize...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.68,0:43:33.19,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们对宇宙以及我们自身的认识\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the way we think about the universe and ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.23,0:43:41.95,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,在此之前 那始终是最大的未解之谜之一\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until then, it remains...one of the greatest unsolved mysteries of all time.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:43.95,0:43:46.37,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将看到外面一个真实的动物园\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And we're going to see a real zoo out there...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:46.41,0:43:48.41,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,一旦我们最终真的发现了外星生命\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when we finally do discover alien life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.45,0:43:51.62,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,各种不同的信息编码的方式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All sorts of different ways of coding information...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.67,0:43:55.46,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,制造出了分子 产生了生命现象\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and making molecules, causing the phenomenon of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.09,0:43:59.80,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,致力于这个领域的人都是怪人\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The people that work on this field are geeks...
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.84,0:44:02.55,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 我们来想象一下与外星怪人的沟通 好吗？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so we imagine making contact with alien geeks, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.59,0:44:05.43,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们将一起愉快地讨论方程式\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that we're going to have fun talking about equations together...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.47,0:44:09.22,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 我们或许会最终与外星时尚人士或嬉皮士接触\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but maybe we'll end up making contact...with alien hipsters or bohemians...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.27,0:44:10.81,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们会需要某些其它论坛\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and we'll need some other forum.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.94,0:44:16.65,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,所以 生命 只是我们不知道\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, life as we don't know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.69,0:44:18.27,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,非常感谢和我的交流\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Thanks very much for talking with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.32,0:44:20.44,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我是塞思·肖斯塔克 来自搜寻地外文明研究所\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}l'm Seth Shostak for the SETl institute...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.49,0:44:21.94,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,我们一直在监听\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where we always listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.99,0:44:23.99,Default,NTP,0,0,0,,但是 偶尔 我们也会广播\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but, occasionally, we broadcast.
